				<li id="16657816" class="cmnt-root" data="7" data-d="1651268218000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578196/Golem's-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">29 Apr 2022 17:36</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16657816" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">They really need to allow changing a weapon&apos;s scaling/affinity while keeping the same ash of war. <br/><br/>This weapon and a few others like the Katar have default skills that really set them apart because they aren&apos;t normally allowed on the weapon class. Katar gets Impaling Thrust, which complements the kit really nicely by giving a far lunge with high stagger to an otherwise quick and short range weapon. The Golem Halberd, similarly, gets Charge Forth (which is already a slept on skill to begin with). This skill does great stagger to begin with, throwing even larger enemies like Omen to the floor if the final hit lands, allowing for a fully charged R2 followup. And on the Golem halberd all of this improves drastically over its use on a spear or halberd. Additionally, colossals benefit greatly from trades and hyperarmor, and since Charge Forth does pierce attacks, you get a sweet counter bonus on top of the already high damage. Lingering attacks are really useful on a large weapon like this, which usually has to deal with being wide open after an attack. And godforbid you miss.<br/><br/>All of that makes for a really unique and fun experience with the weapon, but you&apos;re also locked into no infusions. Seriously, nobody runs standard infusion on their weapons. That&apos;s just the baseline for before you fit it to your build. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16657816" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16657816" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">9</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>16</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>9</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16657816"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16657816" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16657816"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
