				<li id="16523672" class="cmnt-root" data="4" data-d="1647510529000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578196/Golem's-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">17 Mar 2022 05:48</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16523672" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Not sure how good it is as a main weapon, but with my Arcane build I like carrying around an occult version of this for when I need a little extra oomph and crowd control.<br/><br/>Pros:<br/>Can be infused<br/>Very long range (slightly longer than other colossal weapons)<br/>Good moveset with both vertical and horizontal swipes<br/>Can be obtained early on<br/><br/>Cons:<br/>Not exceptional AR<br/>R2 sound currently bugged<br/><br/>P.S. Don&apos;t be scared of the 36 Str - 14 Dex requirements: activating Godrick&apos;s Great Rune or equipping Radagon&apos;s Soreseal allows you to 2h this weeapon with just 19 Str and 9 Dex (or, if you use both, just 14 Str).</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16523672" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16523672" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><secti